<br>
Waldenbooks also stocks the How to Draw Manga books.  Waldenbooks is a national chain of bookstores found primarily in malls.  <br>
<br>
I believe this would classify these books as readily available to many people as there are 7 of said bookstores within a 15 minute radius of where I live.<br>
<br>
Not trying to be a smartass, just pointing out that they are in fact easy to find and about as accessible as the Hart books.  Granted the regular stocking of the HTDM series by Borders and Waldenbooks (who I believe are under the same parent company) is within the last year.<br>
<br>
I have purchased from Borders or Waldens the following books off the shelf:<br>
<br>
HTDM vol 3<br>
HTDM vol 4<br>
HTDAGC vol 2<br>
HTDAGC vol 3<br>
HTDAGC vol 4<br>
<br>
Barnes and Noble doesn't currently stock the HTDM series in their retail stores, to my knowledge. <p>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<br>
